data.text:
Become an Ambassador

The Shaukat Khanum Student Ambassador Programme offers an exceptional opportunity for students to represent the mission of Shaukat Khanum Memorial Cancer Hospital and Research Centre (SKMCH&RC) in their respective colleges or institutes located all across the world. Serving as liaisons between the hospital and their educational institutions, Shaukat Khanum Student Ambassadors gain invaluable hands-on marketing experience, cultivating their leadership and interpersonal skills.

Students currently enrolled in a recognised college/institute from all across the world are eligible to apply.

Apply Online

Note:

If you are unable to submit the online application form successfully, please email us your query at studentambassador@skm.org.pk

Guidelines for Shaukat Khanum Student Ambassador Programme

High school students (overseas) or Students of 11th Grade and above (within Pakistan) currently enrolled in a recognized college/institute are eligible to apply. Applicants must demonstrate a strong academic record and involvement in extracurricular activities.

Candidates must hold at least one affiliation or membership with a club or society within their respective institutes.

Applicants are required to submit the Application Form for review and shortlisting.

Shaukat Khanum Student Ambassadors will be selected for a one-year term, concluding in December.

Ambassadors must engage with us monthly to assist in organizing events and activities in their institutes. Apart from promoting marketing and fundraising campaigns, Ambassadors may organize events such as charity days, bake sales, sports tournaments, cancer awareness walks, or other popular activities in their institutes.

Shaukat Khanum Memorial Trust will provide all necessary promotional materials for organizing these events/activities.

Ambassadors are advised not to accept direct donations from the public except for fundraising activities endorsed by the Hospital. Donors should be guided to submit all donations directly to the Hospital via authorized channels as publicized on https://shaukatkhanum.org.pk/donors/

SKMCH&RC reserves the right to cancel the appointment of ambassadors at any time, at its sole discretion.

Why to join Shaukat Khanum Student Ambassador Programme

Becoming a part of the Shaukat Khanum Student Ambassador Programme not only opens doors for personal and professional development but also provides a unique opportunity to make a significant impact in the lives of those affected by cancer. This esteemed program offers a platform for student ambassadors to experience heightened engagement, motivation, and a sense of empowerment. By embracing their role, Student Ambassadors play a vital part in representing and advancing the mission of the Shaukat Khanum Memorial Cancer Hospital and Research Centre (SKMCH&RC).

Throughout their tenure, Student Ambassadors are offered the following opportunities that further enrich their journey within the organization.

Representing a noble cause

Leadership Development

Enhanced Interpersonal Skills

Professional Growth

Recognition, experience letter, and rewards

Contribution to Community Service

Skills diversification

Access to Hospital Resources

Participation in Hospital events

Career Development Support

Networking Opportunities

Project Leadership opportunities
